cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.SY, cs.NA. 

The paper deals with a data structure for the maintenance of lower envelopes of pseudo-lines, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents a fully dynamic data structure, which involves updating and querying, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions storage space, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The lower envelopes of pseudo-lines are used in control theory, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions an algorithm for finding the intersection between two lower envelopes of pseudo-lines, which involves numerical analysis, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a possible sub-category as well.
